Package: ubuntu-handheld
Version: 1.0
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: gamescope,
         sxhkd,
         acpi-call-dkms,
         python3-venv,
         python3-dev,
         python3-pip,
         build-essential,
         gir1.2-gtk-3.0,
         curl,
         gdm3,
         libfuse2t64,
         libhidapi-hidraw0,
         udev,
         libc6:i386,
         libgl1:i386,
         libgl1-mesa-dri:i386,
         libglx0:i386
Maintainer: ubuntu-handheld contributors
Description: Handheld Ubuntu Setup (SteamOS-like experience)
 Transforms an Ubuntu installation into a console-like handheld gaming
 experience. Installs and configures:
  - Gamescope Steam Gamepad UI as the default boot session
  - Handheld Daemon (HHD) for TDP and controller management
  - HHD overlay for in-game quick access
  - Seamless switching between SteamOS and Ubuntu desktop
  - Virtual keyboard for touchscreen / handheld input
 .
 Remove the package to fully revert to original Ubuntu behaviour.
